Endomorph 1. a mineral, esp. a crystal, enclosed within another  2. a person of the endomorphic physical type characterised by with big bones, round face, large trunk and thighs and a naturally high degree of body fat, especially aroung the midsection.  Endomorphs usually struggle to control their weight although it may simple mean more determination is needed for an endomorph to lose as much weight as a mesomorph.